I think all of these have checked for null.Both LongSum and DoubleSum ,if the value of metrics is null ,it will be converted to 0 int the process of build index.

But not sure all complex like this.

LongMetricColumnSerializer

``` java
 @Override
  public void serialize(Object obj) throws IOException
  {
    long val = (obj == null) ? 0 : ((Number) obj).longValue();
    writer.add(val);
  }
```

HyperUniquesBufferAggregator

``` java
 @Override
  public void aggregate(ByteBuffer buf, int position)
  {
    HyperLogLogCollector collector = (HyperLogLogCollector) selector.get();

    if (collector == null) {
      return;
    }

    HyperLogLogCollector.makeCollector(
        (ByteBuffer) buf.duplicate().position(position).limit(
            position
            + HyperLogLogCollector.getLatestNumBytesForDenseStorage()
        )
    ).fold(collector);
  }
```

HyperUniquesSerde

``` java
    @Override
      public byte[] toBytes(HyperLogLogCollector collector)
      {
        if (collector == null) {
          return new byte[]{};
        }
        ByteBuffer val = collector.toByteBuffer();
        byte[] retVal = new byte[val.remaining()];
        val.asReadOnlyBuffer().get(retVal);
        return retVal;
      }

```

